credits.name: credits
credits.description: Provides you with a list of credits.

feedback.name: feedback
feedback.description: Have any feedback? Use this command!

slap.name: slap
slap.description: Gives a short story to slap someone. There are sometimes consequences though.

spam.name: spam
spam.description: Sends a string of random characters. (Maximum 2000 characters)

gif.name: gif
gif.description: Gives a GIF about a selected string.

xkcd.name: xkcd
xkcd.description: Want to see XKCD comics? Use this command.
xkcd.note: String1 can be random, latest, or a number that specifies to the index of the comic you wanted.

message.name: message
message.description: DMs the user. Shows who sent that message.
message.note: Member1 is the user, and string1 is the content.

private.name: private
private.description: DMs the user. Does not show who sent that message.
private.note: Member1 is the user, and string1 is the content.

say.name: say
say.description: Sends a message in the channel.

secret.name: secret
secret.description: Sends a message in the channel and deletes the original message.

ban.name: ban
ban.description: Bans a user from the server.
ban.note: String1 is the reason for ban.

kick.name: kick
kick.description: Kicks a user from the server.
kick.note: String1 is the reason for kick

warn.name: warn
warn.note: String1 is the reason for warn.

purge.name: purge
purge.note: Integer1 is the amount of texts to be removed (including the message to trigger the command)

badtranslator.name: badtranslator
badtranslator.description: Translate your text into a random language multiple times.
badtranslator.note: Integer1 is the amount of times the text will be translated, whole String1 is the content to be translated.

languagelist.name: languagelist
languagelist.description: Returns a list of languages that can be translated.

translate.name: translate
translate.note: String1 is the target language, while String2 is the content to be translated.

choice.name: choice
choice.description: Choose an option among all choices given.
choice.note: String1 is the question, while list is the choices.

poll.name: poll
poll.note: String1 is the question, while list is the options.

roll.name: roll
roll.description: Rolls a dice and returns the results.
roll.note: If two numbers are given, it would be a XdY roll. Or else it's dX every number.
